JAPAN DAYBOOK: Tokyo Electric Power Seeks Bank Loans

-- B y   S t e v e n   M c P h e r s o n
-- 
2011-03-23T22:29:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/japan-daybook-tokyo-electric-power-seeks-bank-loans.html
Tokyo Electric Power continues
attempts to prevent radiation from escaping damaged reactors and
is said to be seeking loans from three banks.  WHAT TO WATCH
*Tokyo Electric Power (9501 JP) continues attempts to restore
power to cooling systems at nuclear reactors to prevent fuel
rods from melting and releasing radiation. Engineers were
evacuated yesterday after smoke was seen rising from one of the
reactor buildings
*Tokyo Electric Power is said to be in talks with banks for as
much as 2 trillion yen ($25 billion) in loans
*Trade figures for February 8:50 am. Exports forecast +9.1%
*Two-year bond auction results 12:45 pm
*Tokyo gubernatorial campaign begins  EARNINGS
*Askul (2678 JT) nine-months. Full-year net income forecast 2.2
billion yen  ANALYST RATING CHANGES FOR NIKKEI 225 COMPANIES
*Denki Kagaku (4061 JT) raised to outperform at Daiwa.
